OL,3,CTeenager's shock as woman and child
OL,4,Crun through level crossing
OL,6,FResearch commissioned by Network Rail
OL,7,Ffound younger adults are more likely
OL,8,Fto underestimate the speed and power
OL,9,Fof trains, with many admitting to
OL,10,Fdistracted behaviour such as using
OL,11,Fphones, wearing headphones or chatting
OL,12,Fwhile crossing.
OL,14,FIt suggests the majority of those aged
OL,15,F18`34 are unable to recognise key
OL,16,Fwarning signs of an approaching train.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/7
